SENATE BILL 31
C9, F1 6lr0781
(PRE–FILED) CF HB 337
By: Senator Lam
Requested: September 5, 2025
Introduced and read first time: January 14, 2026
Assigned to: Education, Energy, and the Environment
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
Senate action: Adopted
Read second time: March 2, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 School Construction and Housing – School Zones and Adequate Public Facilities
3 Ordinances
4 FOR the purpose of requiring each county board of education to submit a certain report to
5 the Department of Planning and the Interagency Commission on School
6 Construction each year; requiring a county board to consult with certain
7 municipalities and incorporate certain data when developing a local educational
8 facilities master plan; prohibiting certain adequate public facilities ordinances from
9 delaying the processing and completion of subdivision or site development plans;
10 authorizing certain adequate public facilities ordinances to delay the issuance of
11 final permits initiation of construction; and generally relating to school zones, school
12 construction, and adequate public facilities ordinances.
13 BY adding to
14 Article – Education
15 Section 4–148 and 4–149
16 Annotated Code of Maryland
17 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
18 BY adding to
19 Article – Land Use
20 Section 7–106
21 Annotated Code of Maryland
22 (2012 Volume and 2025 Supplement)
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *sb0031*

2 SENATE BILL 31
1 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
2 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
3 Article – Education
4 4–148.
5 (A) ON OR BEFORE JULY 1, 2026, AND EACH JULY 1 THEREAFTER, EACH
6 COUNTY BOARD SHALL SUBMIT A STUDENT RESIDENCY AND SCHOOL ZONES REPORT
7 TO THE DEPARTMENT OF PLANNING AND THE INTERAGENCY COMMISSION ON
8 SCHOOL CONSTRUCTION.
9 (B) (1) THE STUDENT RESIDENCY AND SCHOOL ZONES REPORT SHALL
10 INCLUDE:
11 (I) THE SCHOOL ZONE BOUNDARIES AND ATTENDANCE AREA
12 MAP; AND
13 (II) THE LOCATIONS OF EACH STUDENT’S RESIDENCE; AND
14 (III) THE STATE–RATED CAPACITY, STUDENT POPULATION, AND
15 CAPACITY PERCENTAGE OF EACH SCHOOL IN THE COUNTY CENSUS TRACT AND
16 BLOCK DATA REPORTED TO THE DEPARTMENT IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 4–113.1 OF
17 THIS SUBTITLE.
18 (2) THE REPORT MAY NOT INCLUDE PERSONAL IDENTIFYING
19 INFORMATION OF A STUDENT.
20 (C) THE INTERAGENCY COMMISSION ON SCHOOL CONSTRUCTION SHALL
21 ADOPT REGULATIONS ESTABLISHING FORMATTING AND SUBMISSION
22 REQUIREMENTS FOR THE STUDENT RESIDENCY AND SCHOOL ZONES REPORT.
23 4–149.
24 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “LOCAL EDUCATIONAL FACILITIES MASTER PLAN”
25 MEANS THE ANNUAL PLAN REQUIRED TO BE SUBMITTED TO THE INTERAGENCY
26 COMMISSION ON SCHOOL CONSTRUCTION UNDER COMAR 14.39.02.03.
27 (B) IN DEVELOPING A LOCAL EDUCATIONAL FACILITIES MASTER PLAN, A
28 COUNTY BOARD SHALL:
29 (1) CONSULT WITH EACH MUNICIPALITY LOCATED IN THE COUNTY
30 THAT EXERCISES PLANNING AND ZONING AUTHORITY; AND

SENATE BILL 31 3
1 (2) INCORPORATE DATA PROVIDED BY THE MUNICIPALITIES INTO
2 THE PLAN’S ENROLLMENT PROJECTIONS AND ANALYSIS OF FUTURE FACILITY
3 NEEDS.
4 Article – Land Use
5 7–106.
6 A COUNTY’S IF A COUNTY ENACTS AN ADEQUATE PUBLIC FACILITIES
7 ORDINANCE THAT RESTRICTS HOUSING DEVELOPMENT ON THE BASIS OF SCHOOL
8 CAPACITY INCLUDES A DEFINITE MAXIMUM LENGTH OF TIME TO RESTRICT OR LIMIT
9 HOUSING DEVELOPMENT ON THE BASIS OF SCHOOL CAPACITY, THE ORDINANCE:
10 (1) MAY NOT DELAY THE PROCESSING AND COMPLETION OF
11 SUBDIVISION OR SITE DEVELOPMENT PLANS; BUT
12 (2) MAY DELAY THE ISSUANCE OF FINAL PERMITS INITIATION OF
13 CONSTRUCTION.
14 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
15 1, 2026.
Approved:
